e. I had a mind to copy out your images, all of which ring false, and scathingly juxtapose my infallible observations, but the result would have been “nightmarish nonsense,” as the real Katya would have said, for the Logos allotted me does not possess sufficient precision or power to get disentangled from you. On the contrary, I myself get bogged down in the sticky snares of your conventional descriptions, and have no strength left to liberate Katya from your pen. Nevertheless, like Hamlet, 